attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is an IoT botnet agent, specifically a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt families, targeting MIPS-based Linux devices. The sample contains clear exploit delivery code for the Huawei UPnP SOAP vulnerability (DeviceUpgrade_1), featuring a command injection payload that uses '/bin/busybox wget' to download a secondary stage from 193.233.193.12, saves it as '/tmp/.oxy', and executes it. Additional malicious behaviors include disabling system watchdogs (/dev/watchdog), network scanning via /proc/net/tcp, and process obfuscation techniques. Relevant IOCs include the C2/download IP 193.233.193.12, the file path /tmp/.oxy, and the exploit target URI /ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1.
